definition.value: A member of the class of dibenzoazepines that is the amide formed from formal condensation of the carboxy group of 2,2-dimethyl-3-oxo-3-[(2,2,3,3,3-pentafluoropropyl)amino]propanoic acid with the amino group of (7S)-7-amino-5,7-dihydrodibenzo[b,d]azepin-6-one.
An  O-acylcarnitine in which the acyl group specified is octadecenoyl.
A GDP-4-dehydro-L-fucose in which the anomeric centre of the fucose portion has beta-configuration. An intermediate formed during the de novo synthesis of GDP-L-fucose.
An inorganic sodium salt having sulfite as the counterion.
Heteroorganic entities that are microbial metabolites (or compounds derived from them) which have significant antifungal properties.

A 17-membered homodetic cyclic peptide comprising the sequence -Arg-Thr-Pro-Glu-Asp-Pro-Val-Val-His-Phe-Phe-Tyr-Asp-Ile-Val-Thr-Pro-.  Cyclic analogue with head-to-tail cyclisation of the myelin basic protein 83-99 (MBP83-99) immunodominant epitope with the lysyl residue at position 91 replaced by tyrosyl [MBP83-99(Y(91))].
An O-acylcarnitine in which the acyl group specified is octadecadienoyl.
An organic sodium salt having thioglycolate(1-) as the counterion.
Any antibiotic antifungal agents whose structure is based on the antifungal agents originally isolated from the fungus Strobilurus tenacellus.
A hydrochloride obtained by combining the free base of spirit blue with one equivalent of hydrochloric acid.
Any strobilurin antifungal agent that contains a methoxyacrylate group.
Any strobilurin antifungal agent that contains a methoxycarbanilate group.
An O-acylcarnitine in which the acyl group specified is methylglutaryl.
Any strobilurin antifungal agent that contains a methoxyiminoacetamide group, RC(=NOMe)C(=O)NHMe.
A glycophytoceramide having an alpha-D-galactopyranosyl residue at the O-1 position and an 11-(4-fluorophenyl)undecanoyl group attached to the nitrogen.
Any O-acylcarnitine in which the acyl group contains a total of 4 carbon atoms.
An aromatic amime that is the base component of spirit blue dye (the hydrochloride salt).
Any O-acylcarnitine in which the acyl group contains a total of 5 carbon atoms.
Any O-acylcarnitine in which the acyl group contains a total of 9 carbon atoms.
Heteroorganic entities that are plant metabolites which have significant antifungal properties.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of spirit blue base.

An N-acetyl-amino acid in which the amino acid specified is L-ornithine. If R1 is the acetyl group and R2 is a hydrogen then the molecule is N(5)-acetylornithine. If R1 is a hydrogen and R2 is acetyl group then the molecule is N(2)-acetylornithine.
A hydroxy-amino acid that is kynurenine substituted by a single hydroxy group at unspecified position. A "closed" class.
A hydroxy-amino acid in which the amino acid specified is lysine. A "closed" class.
A hydroxy-amino acid in which the amino acid specified is proline. A "closed" class.
An N-acylglycinate that is the conjugate base of N-myristoylglycine, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.

An EC 1.14.13.* (oxidoreductase acting on paired donors, incorporating 1 atom of oxygen, with NADH or NADPH as one donor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of EC 1.14.13.97 (taurochenodeoxycholate 6alpha-hydroxylase).
A single-stranded DNA oligonucleotide composed of five deoxythymidylic acid residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages and terminated by 3'- and 5'-phosphate groups.
A single-stranded DNA oligonucleotide composed of five deoxythymidylic acid residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages and terminated by a 3'-phosphate group.
A phosphatidylcholine O-36:2 in which the alkyl and acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are hexadecyl and (11Z,14Z)-eicosadienoyl respectively.
A straight-chain polyunsaturated fatty acid composed of eighteen carbons and containing two double bonds, both with Z-geochemistry, at positions 9 and 12 as well as a triple bond at position 6.
An O-acyl-L-carnitine in which the acyl group specified is adipoyl.
An alpha-amino-acid anion that is the  conjugate base of alpha-aminobutyric acid.
A cholestanoid that is cholest-5-ene substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 3 and 26 and oxo groups at positions 16 and 22 respectively.
A glycosphingolipid identical with alpha-galactosylceramide (alpha-GalCer) with the exception of the replacement of the C-2 carbonyl oxygen on the acyl chain with a sulfur atom.
A benzochromenone that is 6H-dibenzo[b,d]pyran substituted by an oxo group at position 6.
A glycosyloxyisoflavone that is calycosin substituted by a beta-D-glucopyranosyl residue at position at 7 via a glycosidic linkage.
A N-acylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as heptadecanoyl.
An N-acylsphingosine in which the acyl group contains 26 carbons and 6 double bonds at unknown positions.
A ceramide phosphoethanolamine in which the sphingoid base and acyl group contains a total of 33 carbon atoms and 1 double bond.
A ceramide phosphoethanolamine (33:1) in which the sphingoid and acyl components are pentadecasphing-4-enine and octadecanoyl respectively.
A ceramide phosphoethanolamine in which the sphingoid base and acyl group contain a total of 34 carbon atoms and 1 double bond.
A N-acyltetradecasphingosine-1-phosphoethanolamine in which the acyl group specified is icosanoyl.
A ceramide phosphoethanolamine in which the sphingoid base and acyl group contains a total of 35 carbon atoms and 1 double bond.
A (2R)-2-methylacyl-CoA(4-) oxanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (2R)-2-methyltetradecanoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3
A (2S)-2-methylacyl-CoA(4-) oxanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (2S)-2-methyltetradecanoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
